				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, averaging each source sample is about as simple as it gets, short of skipping source samples (which is pretty lousy quality). You might be able to specify a higher output rate, like 894886Hz, and let the OS/sound output deal with resampling. I've heard of people using a combination of skipping samples (to reduce it to say 160kHz) and then letting the OS do the rest. There might also be wrappers for whatever sound output you're using (Allegro?) that have a resampler built in.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

