				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Tentatively, I think you've got something else funny going on here. Each time you multiply by 2 you only increase the volume by 6dB, so if it clips when you &lt;&lt;1 and doesn't when you don't, you're already extremely close to the loudest your soundcard can get. Maybe data type issues?<br /><br />The other thing you're doing now is called companding, and that basically can't be done in a way that guarantees it will never clip without either looking ahead in time (1/10th of a second or more) or accepting the volume being non-continuous.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

